results.name: Number of connected trivalent (or cubic) labeled graphs with 2n nodes.
reference: R. C. Read, Some Enumeration Problems in Graph Theory. Ph.D. Dissertation, Department of Mathematics, Univ. London, 1958.
R. W. Robinson, Numerical implementation of graph counting algorithms, AGRC Grant, Math. Dept., Univ. Newcastle, Australia, 1976.
R. W. Robinson, Computer print-out, no date. Gives first 29 terms.
N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100 (terms 1..29 from R. W. Robinson)
R. C. Read, Letter to N. J. A. Sloane, Feb 04 1971 (gives initial terms of this sequence)
R. W. Robinson, Cubic labeled graphs, computer print-out, n.d.
example: For n=3, 2*n=6, the A002851(n)=2 graphs have multiplicities of 10 and 60 (sum 70).

For n=4, 2*n=8, the A002851(n)=5 graphs have multiplicities of 3360, 840, 2520, 10080 and 2520, (sum 19320). (The orders of the five Aut-groups are 8!/3360 =12, 8!/840=48, 8!/2520 =16, 8!/10080=4 and 8!/2520=16, i.e., all larger than 1 as indicated in A204328). (End)
xref: See A002829 for not-necessarily-connected graphs, A002851 for connected unlabeled cases.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_
